The paper proposes a distributed algorithm for multitask reinforcement learning using deep neural networks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of deep neural networks also suggests that the paper may be relevant to the Robotics (cs.RO) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's focus on distributed learning and multi-agent systems suggests that it may also be relevant to the Multiagent Systems (cs.MA) sub-category.
